Baron '''François Narmon''' (26 January 1934 &ndash; 14 March 2013) was a [[Belgium|Belgian]] businessman and president of [[Dexia]] Group and the [[Belgian Olympic Committee]].<ref>Véronique POUILLARD, (1999), "François Narmon" in Cent grands patrons du vingtième siècle en Belgique,E. Buyst- G.- Kurgan-van Hentenryk éd., Bruxelles, A. Renier, pp.&nbsp;164–165.</ref> From 2002 until 2004 he was a member of the [[International Olympic Committee]].
Born in [[Jette]], Narmon obtained a licentiate degree as commercial engineer from the [[Université libre de Bruxelles]] ([[Solvay Business School|École de commerce Solvay]]). He lectured on [[accountancy]] at the Université libre de Bruxelles and the [[Vrije Universiteit Brussel]], and made the local ''Gemeentekrediet'' into the financial enterprise [[Dexia]]. He died on 14 March 2013 in [[Meise]].
