{{Infobox serial killer | name= Genzo Kurita | image= | caption= | birthname= Genzo Kurita | alias= | birth_date={{Birth date|1926|11|03}} | birth_place=[[Akita Prefecture|Akita]], [[Japan]] | death_date={{Death date and age|1959|10|14|1926|11|03}} | cause=[[hanging]] | victims=8 | country=[[Japan]] | states=[[Chiba Prefecture|Chiba]], [[Tochigi Prefecture|Tochigi]], [[Shizuoka Prefecture|Shizuoka]] | beginyear=February 1948 | endyear=January 13, 1952 | apprehended=January 16, 1952 | penalty=[[Death penalty|Death]] }} {{nihongo|'''Genzo Kurita'''|栗田 源蔵|''Kurita Genzō''|extra=November 3, 1926 – October 14, 1959|lead=yes}} was a [[Japanese people|Japanese]] [[serial killer]] who murdered eight people.
== Murders == Kurita [[murder]]ed two girlfriends in February 1948. On August 8, 1951, he [[rape]]d and murdered a 24-year-old woman beside her baby. He then had [[Necrophilia|sex with her corpse]].{{citation needed|date=April 2017}}
On October 11, 1951, he raped and murdered a 29-year-old woman. He threw her three children from a [[cliff]] called [[Osen Korogashi]]. One survived.{{citation needed|date=April 2017}}
Kurita killed a 63-year-old woman and her 24-year-old niece on January 13, 1952. Afterward, he had sex with the niece's dead body. At the crime scene, the police found his [[fingerprint]]s.{{citation needed|date=April 2017}}
== Arrest, trial, and execution == Kurita was arrested on January 16, 1952.{{citation needed|date=April 2017}}
On August 12, 1952, the district court in Chiba [[death penalty|sentenced him to death]] for the last two murders. The district court in Utsunomiya sentenced him to death for six others on December 21, 1953. He [[appeal]]ed the sentences, but because of mental instability he retracted his appeals on October 21, 1954. He was considered to be [[neurosis|neurotic]] and a danger to himself. He was executed on October 14, 1959.{{citation needed|date=April 2017}}
== Aftermath == On May 10, 1956, a pro-[[death penalty]] prosecutor in Supreme Public Prosecutors Office introduced Kurita into a debate about capital punishment in the [[Diet of Japan|Diet]].<ref>{{cite web | author= | script-title=ja:第024回国会 法務委員会公聴会 第2号 | publisher=[[National Diet Library]] | language=Japanese | url=http://kokkai.ndl.go.jp/SENTAKU/sangiin/024/0640/02405100640002c.html | date=1956-05-10 | accessdate=2008-01-09}}</ref>
